In 2006 Sancho became the first Gillingham player ever to play in the [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup finals]], and technically the first to score in the World Cup finals when he scored an [[own goal]] in the [[2006 FIFA World Cup - Group B|2-0 group defeat]] to [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]].<ref>{{Cite web
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/world_cup_2006/4853292.stm
